node.text: Working in restaurants, Lan Lam learned a ton of useful information, including how to open beer with pretty much anything.

node.text: Blueberry and lemon provide complementary brightness and warmth in this easy, naturally-sweetened tart. Blueberry-Lemon Curd Tart recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 08, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: For breaded chicken cutlets that are not only perfectly cooked but also easier to make, ditch the classic breading technique and think about crumb size. Crispy Pan-Fried Chicken Cutlets recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 08, 2021.

node.text: Cleaning your gas grill isn't glamorous, but it is necessary. Don't know where to start? One of our test cooks walks you through the process. Click the link in our profile for our guide to deep cleaning your gas grill.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 08, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: Bone-in short ribs are perfect for braising: When cooked slowly, they boast a rich, beefy flavor and a tender, velvety texture. Braised Short Ribs with Wild Mushroom Farrotto recipe link in profile.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 08, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: Want to up your breakfast game? Add ricotta to your pancakes for results that are both fluffier and tastier. Click the link in our profile to find out how.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 08, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: The trendy multipurpose Always Pan has earned accolades from the likes of Vogue, Food & Wine, and so many bloggers, but does it stand up to our tests? Click the link in our profile to find out.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 07, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: Pantry staples and a familiar kitchen tool are the keys to a smooth, flavorful soup. Red Lentil Soup with North African Spices recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 07, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and pasta.

node.text: Here’s our weeknight, quick Bolognese sauce that rivals the depth and richness of long-cooked versions. Weeknight Tagliatelle with Bolognese Sauce recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 07, 2021. May be an image of drink and food.

node.text: Quench your thirst with this refreshing drink. Blend chunks of watermelon with water in a blender and strain out the pulp before accenting the mixture with lime juice, agave nectar, and a pinch of salt to bring out the sweet and tart flavors. Watermelon-Lime Agua Fresca recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 07, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: Spanakopita is a Greek spinach-and-cheese pie with a crisp phyllo shell. Here’s how we transformed the dish for cooking in one skillet. Skillet Spanakopita recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 06, 2021. May be an image of pizza.

node.text: Lasagna purists might be surprised to find that we swapped some traditional ingredients for more flavorful (trust us) ingredients, such as cottage cheese, fontina, and parmesan. Our members call it “a keeper” and “the BEST lasagna I’ve ever tasted.” Cheese and Tomato Lasagna recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 06, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: To make grilled cauliflower with a tender interior and a flavorful, nicely browned exterior, we first microwaved it until it was cooked through and then briefly grilled it to pick up color and flavor. Grilled Cauliflower recipe link in bio.
